WEBVTT

00:00.317 --> 00:02.818
Usic]

00:02.903 --> 00:03.986
[seagulls calling, bells ring]

00:04.071 --> 00:07.106
[distant foghorn blares]

00:09.827 --> 00:11.727
- hey, tony,
where you headed?

00:11.829 --> 00:14.396
- I hear the white perch
are schooled up.

00:14.498 --> 00:16.898
Maybe look for some mackerel
the east end of the canal.

00:17.001 --> 00:18.734
- Be careful when you head out,
okay?

00:18.836 --> 00:22.121
There's another big storm
headed in due south.

00:22.206 --> 00:24.239
It's messing with the tides.
See you.

00:24.341 --> 00:25.741
- Thanks.

00:25.843 --> 00:28.744
<i> [ominous music]</i>

00:28.846 --> 00:30.379
[motor humming]

00:32.683 --> 00:38.387
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:43.527 --> 00:45.611
[rumbles]

00:46.697 --> 00:47.396
I think we hit something.

00:51.402 --> 00:57.539
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:01.412 --> 01:02.110
oh, shit.

01:02.213 --> 01:03.829
- [gasps]

01:03.914 --> 01:06.632
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:15.509 --> 01:17.509
<i> - next order of business:</i>

01:17.595 --> 01:20.262
<i> The home at 29 commercial</i>

01:20.347 --> 01:22.765
is requesting permission
to change their shingles

01:22.850 --> 01:25.350
from our traditional
"simply white"

01:25.436 --> 01:27.686
to "mountain peak white."

01:27.772 --> 01:28.821
- can we see the samples?

01:30.908 --> 01:32.808
- Have you lost your mind?

01:32.910 --> 01:34.693
- It's a scandal
that you would even ask.

01:34.779 --> 01:36.478
- Why don't you just
paint them orange?

01:36.580 --> 01:37.362
[laughter]

01:37.448 --> 01:39.448
[gavel slams]
- motion denied.

01:40.618 --> 01:43.202
Next order of business:

01:43.287 --> 01:46.038
Jim levy,
the owner of mchenry's,

01:46.123 --> 01:47.790
is requesting
a 16-inch easement

01:47.875 --> 01:49.374
into the neighbor's green area

01:49.460 --> 01:52.377
so he can have
expanded outdoor dining.

01:52.463 --> 01:55.881
I believe mr. Levy
is present to make his case.

01:55.966 --> 01:57.266
- Thank you, madam.

01:58.469 --> 02:00.135
As most of you know,
I opened mchenry's

02:00.221 --> 02:01.804
as sister restaurant

02:01.889 --> 02:04.640
to my flagship mchenry's
in davis square, somerville.

02:04.725 --> 02:06.308
- Can it, levy.
You're wasting your time.

02:06.393 --> 02:07.893
- Excuse me?
- Well,

02:07.978 --> 02:09.812
first of all,
your name is levy.

02:09.897 --> 02:10.979
I don't know where you get off

02:11.065 --> 02:13.315
owning not one
but two irish pubs.

02:13.400 --> 02:14.349
That's called cultural
appropriation, sweetheart.

02:14.451 --> 02:17.202
Second of all,
you have terrible taste.

02:17.321 --> 02:18.537
And not just in your footwear.

02:18.656 --> 02:20.539
My friend mitch wilson

02:20.658 --> 02:21.990
lives in the house
next to your restaurant.

02:22.076 --> 02:24.376
He has exquisite taste.

02:24.495 --> 02:25.878
And the last thing we need

02:25.996 --> 02:28.330
are your cheap plastic
tables and chairs

02:28.415 --> 02:30.165
soiling his hydrangea bushes.

02:30.251 --> 02:31.750
[gavel slams]
- motion denied.

02:31.836 --> 02:32.668
- But--
- denied.

02:32.753 --> 02:33.552
- Come on, he's be--
- denied.

02:36.924 --> 02:41.260
Finally, trooper remy
of the mass state police

02:41.345 --> 02:43.428
would like a moment
to speak to the group.

02:43.514 --> 02:47.566
<i> [ominous music]</i>

02:47.685 --> 02:50.686
- chairwoman, council,
I'm trooper jan remy.

02:50.771 --> 02:53.188
I was sent by the state police
to run the investigation

02:53.274 --> 02:54.690
into your murdered chief.

02:54.775 --> 02:56.325
- I thought the chief
was just missing?

02:56.410 --> 02:58.076
- She was,

02:58.195 --> 03:00.078
until a fisherman ran over
her body in the harbor.

03:00.197 --> 03:02.030
<i> [chilling tone]</i>

03:02.116 --> 03:03.532
and something you all
may not know

03:03.617 --> 03:05.200
is that the chief
was investigating

03:05.286 --> 03:08.086
a series of murders.

03:08.205 --> 03:09.004
They all followed
the same m.O.--

03:11.041 --> 03:15.427
Throat slashed
with severe uneven wounds,

03:15.546 --> 03:17.713
and a draining of almost all
of the victim's blood.

03:20.100 --> 03:21.683
I just examined
the chief's body

03:21.769 --> 03:25.520
and observed
the exact same wound pattern.

03:25.606 --> 03:27.639
- Boat propeller
could have chewed her up.

03:28.893 --> 03:30.559
- Lotta sharks in the water
at this time.

03:30.644 --> 03:33.228
- Which is why need to stop
protecting the seals.

03:33.314 --> 03:35.230
- I don't mind the sharks

03:35.316 --> 03:36.732
as long as they're only killing
yankee fans.

03:36.817 --> 03:38.617
[laughter]

03:38.736 --> 03:40.285
- I'm sorry,
but this isn't funny.

03:40.404 --> 03:43.622
A law enforcement officer
was murdered

03:43.741 --> 03:45.874
by what appears to be
a serial killer.

03:45.960 --> 03:48.293
- Do you have proof
that these cases are related?

03:48.412 --> 03:49.544
Right? Dna?

03:49.630 --> 03:51.129
- Not yet.

03:51.248 --> 03:52.631
- I just don't know why
we would make a big fuss

03:52.750 --> 03:54.549
when we don't even know
if there's a problem.

03:54.635 --> 03:55.634
- Your chief
was brutally murdered

03:55.753 --> 03:57.719
and thrown in the harbor.

03:57.805 --> 03:58.954
I'd say that's a problem.

03:59.056 --> 04:01.723
- I mean, do we even know
she was murdered?

04:01.809 --> 04:02.724
- Maybe she went
for a night swim.

04:02.810 --> 04:05.644
- In her uniform?

04:05.763 --> 04:09.481
And many of these murders
occurred miles from the ocean.

04:09.600 --> 04:12.150
Do you think the sharks
and the boat propellers

04:12.269 --> 04:15.821
somehow came on land
to kill all these people?

04:15.940 --> 04:18.407
- Look, trooper.

04:18.492 --> 04:20.242
We really appreciate
what you're trying to do here.

04:20.327 --> 04:23.245
Mass state police
are a wonderful organization

04:23.330 --> 04:24.813
full of fine men and women.

04:24.915 --> 04:25.330
- Absolutely.
- Hear, hear.

04:25.449 --> 04:27.148
[light clapping]

04:27.251 --> 04:29.084
but these
are wintertime problems.

04:29.169 --> 04:32.087
- What does that mean?
- It means strange things

04:32.172 --> 04:34.089
happen down the cape
in the winter.

04:34.174 --> 04:35.757
Everyone knows it.

04:35.843 --> 04:37.509
Us full-timers just accept it

04:37.628 --> 04:42.097
as the price of living
in such a special place.

04:42.182 --> 04:44.766
But by the time
spring rolls around,

04:44.852 --> 04:48.603
you'll see
it all just magically stops.

04:48.689 --> 04:50.772
And the worst problem we have?

04:50.858 --> 04:51.840
Uh, traffic on route 6,

04:51.942 --> 04:54.776
a bad sunburn,

04:54.862 --> 04:56.177
and too much butter
on a lobster roll.

04:56.280 --> 04:57.729
[laughter]

04:57.815 --> 05:01.182
- so you're saying
I should just let this go?

05:01.285 --> 05:02.401
- We're saying
that everyone in this room

05:02.486 --> 05:05.186
depends upon the summer
to pay for the winter.

05:05.289 --> 05:06.688
We are saying

05:06.790 --> 05:09.024
that if you start
making noise about this stuff,

05:09.126 --> 05:10.692
maybe the papers in boston
will pick it up,

05:10.794 --> 05:12.360
and then the new york rags,

05:12.463 --> 05:14.029
and then suddenly,
all of those city-folk

05:14.131 --> 05:15.864
who drive down
for the weekend in July

05:15.966 --> 05:17.632
to spend all of that
sweet city money

05:17.718 --> 05:20.035
get spooked
and decide that maybe

05:20.137 --> 05:21.536
the berkshires,
or newport,

05:21.638 --> 05:24.589
or--god forbid--
the hamptons are just as nice.

05:24.675 --> 05:27.259
But not worth
all the trouble and the worry.

05:27.344 --> 05:29.428
- The gays might stop coming.

05:29.513 --> 05:31.013
<i> [chilling tone]</i>

05:32.016 --> 05:34.215
- you're all hiding something.

05:34.318 --> 05:36.051
You know something.

05:36.153 --> 05:37.819
- We know what's best
for this community.

05:37.905 --> 05:39.321
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:39.406 --> 05:40.989
we know what's best for you.

05:41.075 --> 05:42.824
- I was sent by
the state of massachusetts

05:42.910 --> 05:45.226
to come down here and find
out what's been going on,

05:45.329 --> 05:48.063
and that's what I'm gonna do.

05:48.165 --> 05:51.116
Impeding an investigation
is a crime.

05:51.201 --> 05:52.784
And they don't serve
lobster rolls

05:52.870 --> 05:54.235
in walpole state prison.

05:54.338 --> 06:01.626
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:01.712 --> 06:02.511
[door slams]

06:06.350 --> 06:06.715
- don't worry.

06:08.719 --> 06:09.217
I'll take care of it.

06:09.303 --> 06:11.770
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:13.023 --> 06:15.924
<i> [chilling music]</i>

06:16.026 --> 06:23.031
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:41.752 --> 06:47.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:02.189 --> 07:09.244
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:18.655 --> 07:20.455
<i> - look,</i>

07:20.574 --> 07:23.458
we have been extremely patient
and understanding

07:23.577 --> 07:25.577
about this whole business
with the pills

07:25.662 --> 07:26.628
and the blood drinking.

07:26.747 --> 07:28.580
I mean, the pales
recede into the woods

07:28.665 --> 07:30.132
during the summer,

07:30.250 --> 07:32.250
and you gluttons
don't feed on anybody

07:32.352 --> 07:33.919
who actual matters
in this town.

07:34.004 --> 07:35.587
- And we don't feed
past memorial day.

07:35.689 --> 07:37.672
- Yes.
The system has held.

07:37.758 --> 07:39.174
It's a symbiosis.

07:39.259 --> 07:40.675
You get the freedom
and the quiet

07:40.761 --> 07:43.595
to write and kill,
and we get to brag

07:43.680 --> 07:45.347
about having artists make
their winter home out here.

07:45.432 --> 07:47.015
It adds to the charm.

07:47.100 --> 07:50.435
But this winter has been
completely out of control.

07:50.521 --> 07:52.103
I mean,
you killed the chief.

07:52.189 --> 07:53.989
If that isn't the worst example
of shitting where you eat,

07:54.107 --> 07:55.407
I don't know what is.

07:55.492 --> 07:57.659
- It's not us.
It's the hollywood people.

07:57.778 --> 07:58.810
They ruin everything.
- It's true.

07:58.912 --> 08:01.163
- Belle and I
are people of the letters.

08:01.281 --> 08:03.081
Literature, the stage--
these are art forms that demand

08:03.167 --> 08:05.450
a degree of decorum and
restraint from their purveyors.

08:05.536 --> 08:07.619
These fucking hollywood people
have no decency.

08:07.704 --> 08:10.455
- And no self-control.

08:10.541 --> 08:12.624
That beast of a man
gave the pills to his child.

08:12.709 --> 08:15.627
It makes you think that maybe
some of that qanon business

08:15.712 --> 08:17.512
about them being satanic
baby-killers

08:17.631 --> 08:18.964
is based in some fact.

08:19.049 --> 08:22.517
- All I know is I told you two
to get rid of him days ago.

08:22.636 --> 08:24.102
- I've been very busy.
I'm on a deadline.

08:24.188 --> 08:25.220
- Yeah, well,
so are we.

08:25.305 --> 08:27.856
The council asked me
to convey a message:

08:27.975 --> 08:30.942
"get rid of the troublemakers,
or all of you

08:31.028 --> 08:32.611
are suddenly
gonna find yourself

08:32.696 --> 08:34.779
going into some very
annoying zoning issues,

08:34.865 --> 08:36.865
including painting
all of the curbs

08:36.984 --> 08:39.034
in front of your houses red

08:39.152 --> 08:41.703
and declaring all of your
domiciles as historic landmarks

08:41.822 --> 08:44.372
which means
that even to change a bulb

08:44.491 --> 08:46.041
will take a six-week
approval process.

08:46.159 --> 08:50.712
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:50.831 --> 08:54.216
you know, I stopped burger king
from opening in this town.

08:54.334 --> 08:56.051
I can stop you too.

08:56.169 --> 08:59.304
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:59.389 --> 09:00.305
[door shuts]

09:00.390 --> 09:02.807
- [sighs]
so what's the plan?

09:02.893 --> 09:04.142
- [chuckles]

09:04.228 --> 09:09.681
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:25.082 --> 09:26.064
- so what do you think?

09:26.166 --> 09:27.949
- Well...

09:29.920 --> 09:31.036
I think you should
kill yourself.

09:32.756 --> 09:36.341
Because you will never
write anything this good--

09:36.426 --> 09:38.343
no one will.
No one has.

09:38.428 --> 09:40.011
- Good,
I'm glad you like it.

09:40.097 --> 09:42.747
I'm kind of proud of it.
- This is really it, harry.

09:42.849 --> 09:44.015
I mean,
this is your masterpiece.

09:44.101 --> 09:45.850
It's your "moby dick,"

09:45.936 --> 09:47.519
your "romeo and juliet,"
your "godfather."

09:47.604 --> 09:48.887
- thanks,
I know.

09:51.525 --> 09:53.925
Which is why I need to make
a family announcement.

09:54.027 --> 09:56.027
Now that spring is coming,

09:56.113 --> 09:58.363
and I've written basically
five years' worth of stuff

09:58.448 --> 10:00.115
since we've been here...

10:00.233 --> 10:01.149
[breathes deeply]

10:02.736 --> 10:04.319
we're done.

10:06.123 --> 10:06.871
- Done with what?

10:06.957 --> 10:09.124
- With the pills.

10:09.242 --> 10:10.458
It's been a fun ride,

10:10.577 --> 10:13.461
but it's time to get off
this crazy train.

10:13.580 --> 10:16.131
- You mean until next winter,
right?

10:16.249 --> 10:17.966
- I mean for good.

10:18.085 --> 10:19.884
- So now that you're done
with your masterpiece,

10:19.970 --> 10:21.469
we all have to stop?

10:21.588 --> 10:23.305
- It's not like that.
- It's exactly like that.

10:23.423 --> 10:25.223
You're being selfish.
- I'm being a father.

10:25.309 --> 10:26.424
- All of a sudden?
- Don't say that.

10:26.510 --> 10:28.893
After everything
I've done for you this winter--

10:28.979 --> 10:29.961
bringing you
thermoses of blood,

10:30.063 --> 10:31.462
not grounding you for life

10:31.565 --> 10:33.398
for giving your mother a pill
and condemning her

10:33.483 --> 10:35.133
to the misery
of those pale people.

10:35.235 --> 10:36.401
- That wasn't just for me.

10:36.486 --> 10:37.902
You did all of that
for you too!

10:37.988 --> 10:40.271
<i> [intense music]</i>

10:42.326 --> 10:43.908
tell him he's wrong.

10:43.994 --> 10:47.812
Tell him that we can't stop,
that we don't have to stop.

10:47.914 --> 10:49.814
That we're better
than everybody else.

10:49.916 --> 10:52.000
That no one else matters
but people like us.

10:53.286 --> 10:54.536
- Well, there is some
truth to that, sweetheart.

10:54.621 --> 10:56.154
There's a lot of truth.

10:56.256 --> 10:58.423
Harry, you don't take
your foot off the gas

10:58.508 --> 11:00.925
just as you're pulling out
into the lead.

11:01.011 --> 11:01.960
- I don't want
to have to kill anymore.

11:03.930 --> 11:05.096
I just want to raise you
and enjoy the fruits

11:05.182 --> 11:07.665
of what we've accomplished
this year

11:07.768 --> 11:10.769
and maybe over time
get some of my soul back.

11:10.854 --> 11:13.104
- Yeah, it doesn't
work that way, bubbulah.

11:13.190 --> 11:15.774
Once you sell your soul,
it's gone.

11:15.859 --> 11:16.975
- I don't want to believe that.

11:17.060 --> 11:19.177
- Because you're framing it
as a bad thing,

11:19.279 --> 11:21.345
but it is not.
It's freedom.

11:21.448 --> 11:23.181
Why have a conscience
or a moral code anymore?

11:23.283 --> 11:25.950
You're above all of that.

11:26.036 --> 11:28.620
This is what success
feels like, harry,

11:28.705 --> 11:29.687
it feels like superiority.

11:29.790 --> 11:31.689
<i> [dark music]</i>

11:31.792 --> 11:33.575
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:33.660 --> 11:36.194
- alma, I believe in you.

11:36.296 --> 11:37.695
You are better
at playing your violin

11:37.798 --> 11:40.364
than most of us
will ever be at anything.

11:40.467 --> 11:42.250
And now I can be home
all the time

11:42.335 --> 11:44.202
with no distractions
to support your dreams.

11:44.304 --> 11:47.205
I can just be a dad
to you and your brother.

11:47.307 --> 11:49.207
We can do this the right way.

11:49.309 --> 11:51.259
You just have to trust me.

11:51.344 --> 11:54.345
<i> [soft music]</i>

11:54.431 --> 11:55.680
- okay.

11:55.766 --> 11:56.765
- [scoffs quietly]

11:56.850 --> 11:59.768
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:59.853 --> 12:01.052
- I love you so much, honey.

12:01.154 --> 12:02.687
- I love you too, daddy.

12:03.990 --> 12:06.891
<i> [dark, ominous music]</i>

12:06.993 --> 12:10.912
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:22.509 --> 12:25.794
- insane brainz memory boost.

12:25.879 --> 12:27.128
- It's supposed to be
cutting edge.

12:27.214 --> 12:28.797
- I guess it's because "brains"
is spelled with a z

12:28.882 --> 12:30.248
instead of an s.

12:30.350 --> 12:31.716
I feel the boost already.

12:31.802 --> 12:33.718
- [forced laughter]

12:33.804 --> 12:35.220
- you really think vitamins
are gonna make up

12:35.305 --> 12:37.722
for the black pills?
- I didn't say that.

12:37.808 --> 12:39.474
I just think the transition's
gonna be hard for us,

12:39.559 --> 12:41.559
and it can't hurt
to be as healthy--

12:41.645 --> 12:42.310
<i> [eerie tone]</i>

12:42.395 --> 12:47.565
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:47.651 --> 12:50.118
- what?
- I thought I saw her.

12:51.488 --> 12:54.289
- [sighs]
dad, you gotta let her go.

12:54.407 --> 12:55.623
- [scoffs]

12:55.742 --> 12:58.126
she's not some stray cat
that shows up on your porch.

12:58.245 --> 13:01.246
You're talking about
your mother.

13:01.331 --> 13:03.331
That's your mother out there.
- She isn't anything anymore.

13:03.416 --> 13:05.049
She's not even a person.

13:06.002 --> 13:07.135
- Whoever it was is gone.

13:11.258 --> 13:13.007
- Dad?

13:13.093 --> 13:14.476
Did someone break in?

13:16.680 --> 13:17.628
[ursula speaking indistinctly]

13:17.731 --> 13:18.680
kay,
you throw another number out.

13:18.765 --> 13:19.931
I'm gonna fly out there
and kick you

13:20.016 --> 13:21.015
in the fucking face.
- Ursula!

13:21.101 --> 13:22.767
- Hang on.
What?

13:22.853 --> 13:24.018
- The kitchen door--
it looks like someone broke in.

13:24.104 --> 13:25.270
- Broke in?

13:25.355 --> 13:25.987
Francis,
I have to call you back.

13:26.106 --> 13:28.690
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

13:28.775 --> 13:32.944
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:33.029 --> 13:34.445
<i> [chilling tone]</i>

13:36.366 --> 13:38.333
<i> - I know good help</i>
<i> is hard to find,</i>

13:38.451 --> 13:39.784
<i> but you really should</i>
<i> look into</i>

13:39.870 --> 13:41.452
<i> a new babysitter.</i>
<i> [chuckling]</i>

13:41.538 --> 13:42.837
<i> in the meantime,</i>
<i> I've taken it on myself</i>

13:42.956 --> 13:45.290
<i> to look after</i>
<i> the little bundle of joy.</i>

13:45.375 --> 13:46.291
<i> Don't worry,</i>
<i> he'll be safe and sound</i>

13:46.376 --> 13:47.959
<i> and snug as a bug.</i>

13:48.044 --> 13:49.677
<i> But if you aren't at my house</i>
<i> by sunset,</i>

13:49.796 --> 13:51.679
<i> that will change.</i>

13:51.798 --> 13:55.850
Ps: Make sure you bring
the string plucker.

13:55.969 --> 13:57.435
