If we wanna keep it up,

26:23.699 --> 26:24.648
we've gotta be
in the volume business.

26:24.734 --> 26:26.867
- You're creating
a lot of pale people.

26:26.953 --> 26:29.620
Especially pushing pills
at a starbucks.

26:29.739 --> 26:32.289
No self-respecting writer
writes at a starbucks.

26:32.408 --> 26:33.540
- So what?
If they're talentless,

26:33.626 --> 26:34.959
they're useless anyway.

26:35.077 --> 26:36.460
- That's my girl.

26:36.579 --> 26:37.828
- I can't believe
you turned out so well

26:37.913 --> 26:41.131
being raised by harry and that
glass of warm oat milk.

26:41.250 --> 26:42.633
How's the practicing?

26:42.752 --> 26:44.951
- Good.
I'm ready.

26:45.054 --> 26:47.788
- I know you're gonna get it,
sweetheart.

26:47.890 --> 26:49.289
- I could use something to eat
before I go, though.

26:49.392 --> 26:51.725
- Oh, I picked up a hustler

26:51.811 --> 26:53.894
from that donut shop
on santa monica and highland.

26:53.980 --> 26:55.012
He's out in the pool house.

26:56.232 --> 26:58.515
You look adorable.

26:58.601 --> 26:59.650
Proud of you.

26:59.769 --> 27:02.152
- Oh, did you get donuts?
- Of course I did.

27:03.272 --> 27:05.689
<i> [ominous music]</i>

27:05.775 --> 27:06.991
- oh.

27:08.411 --> 27:10.977
Not what I was expecting.

27:11.080 --> 27:13.530
- Me neither.
But I'll take it.

27:13.616 --> 27:16.533
<i> [violin music playing]</i>

27:16.619 --> 27:23.674
♪ ♪

27:34.854 --> 27:40.891
♪ ♪

27:49.952 --> 27:50.901
[violin playing ceases]

27:50.986 --> 27:53.904
<i> [subtle, dark music]</i>

27:53.989 --> 27:59.960
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:01.247 --> 28:03.047
- take a seat.

28:04.750 --> 28:07.418
All right,
it's down to the two of you.

28:07.503 --> 28:09.670
So just sit tight
so the team can chat.

28:09.755 --> 28:10.921
Won't be too long.

28:11.006 --> 28:12.756
Though,
to be honest,

28:12.842 --> 28:15.759
you're making it
a very hard choice.

28:15.845 --> 28:16.977
You're both wonderful.

28:24.520 --> 28:26.103
- So...

28:26.188 --> 28:27.771
How long have you been playing?

28:27.857 --> 28:29.106
And don't say,
"since I was a kid."

28:29.191 --> 28:30.107
- I'm better than you.

28:30.192 --> 28:31.275
- Excuse me?

28:31.360 --> 28:33.277
- I said I'm better than you.

28:33.362 --> 28:34.728
- Did you listen
to my audition?

28:34.830 --> 28:35.896
- No.

28:35.998 --> 28:37.230
I didn't have to.
I know I'm better than you.

28:37.333 --> 28:39.783
I'm better than everyone.

28:39.869 --> 28:40.584
- [laughs]

28:41.537 --> 28:43.754
wow,
you are something else.

28:45.958 --> 28:47.875
I'm a prodigy too.

28:47.960 --> 28:50.127
Graduated juilliard
when I was 16.

28:50.212 --> 28:52.129
You're new to this game,

28:52.214 --> 28:52.963
but what you'll
start to realize

28:53.048 --> 28:54.798
is that there are lots of us.

28:54.884 --> 28:56.967
Most of the players in the big
philharmonics were prodigies.

28:57.052 --> 28:59.386
It's not as big a deal
once you meet others like you.

28:59.472 --> 29:01.605
- There are no others like me.

29:01.724 --> 29:03.223
- I guess that's true,

29:03.309 --> 29:04.892
but you think
that's a good thing.

29:04.977 --> 29:07.611
It's actually why you're
not going to get this job.

29:07.730 --> 29:09.947
<i> [tense tone]</i>

29:10.065 --> 29:13.233
if you get first chair,
it's a huge story.

29:13.319 --> 29:15.235
"today show,"
"people" magazine,

29:15.321 --> 29:17.070
"60 minutes" maybe,
if it's a slow news month.

29:17.156 --> 29:19.239
You're a novelty.
A distraction.

29:19.325 --> 29:21.458
Audiences will come to see you

29:21.577 --> 29:23.627
and get bummed out
if you're not featured.

29:23.746 --> 29:26.079
It's bad for morale.

29:26.165 --> 29:28.132
Makes it impossible
to play anything

29:28.250 --> 29:30.384
that doesn't have
a violin solo.

29:31.086 --> 29:32.219
It becomes a freakshow.

29:34.089 --> 29:35.172
<i> [tense string music]</i>

29:35.257 --> 29:36.757
we play classical music.

29:36.842 --> 29:39.092
We are as square as we can be.

29:39.178 --> 29:41.094
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:41.180 --> 29:43.096
you're the bearded
fucking lady, kid.

29:43.182 --> 29:47.184
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:47.269 --> 29:49.903
<i> [music darkens]</i>

29:51.440 --> 29:52.773
what?

29:52.858 --> 29:58.912
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:07.706 --> 30:09.623
- where'd rory go?

30:09.708 --> 30:11.341
- He said he was going out back
to have a cigarette.

30:11.460 --> 30:18.465
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:23.222 --> 30:29.443
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:31.230 --> 30:34.147
- [screams]

30:34.233 --> 30:40.037
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:43.142 --> 30:45.275
- talent rises,

30:45.394 --> 30:47.277
but it is nothing
without craft.

30:47.396 --> 30:50.063
That's why you need
the story prism.

30:50.149 --> 30:51.398
<i> [eerie string notes]</i>

30:51.483 --> 30:54.117
the story prism is hard
like a diamond.

30:54.236 --> 30:55.702
It takes commitment.

30:57.656 --> 30:58.405
You.
Stand up.

30:59.992 --> 31:01.575
You look confused.

31:01.677 --> 31:03.627
- I still don't understand
the difference between

31:03.746 --> 31:05.462
the primal defense co-tagonist

31:05.581 --> 31:07.965
or the shadow-trickster
pre-tagonist.

31:08.083 --> 31:10.801
Why does it have to be
so complicated?

31:10.920 --> 31:14.137
- Because drama is life
and life is complicated.

31:14.256 --> 31:15.889
Now get the fuck out.

31:15.975 --> 31:16.924
He'll never amount
to anything.

31:17.009 --> 31:18.475
He's never gonna write
a screenplay

31:18.594 --> 31:20.310
that gleams like a diamond.
And full refund.

31:20.429 --> 31:22.729
He's gonna need
every penny he's got.

31:22.815 --> 31:24.648
- Screw you.

31:24.767 --> 31:26.350
[door shuts]

31:27.519 --> 31:29.653
now for the rest of us,
I have a surprise.

31:29.772 --> 31:31.738
I told you when you
finished my seminar

31:31.824 --> 31:35.158
you would walk out
of this building changed.

31:35.277 --> 31:38.662
Well,
get ready to meet someone.

31:38.781 --> 31:40.664
Her client,
the late harry gardener,

31:40.783 --> 31:42.332
just swept the awards season.

31:42.451 --> 31:44.084
And in the last six months,

31:44.169 --> 31:45.419
other clients
have barnstormed this town.

31:45.504 --> 31:47.588
They're launching projects
all over

31:47.673 --> 31:49.172
broadcast and streaming.

31:49.291 --> 31:52.259
It's an unprecedented
winning streak.

31:52.344 --> 31:54.344
Ursula khan.

31:54.463 --> 31:56.847
[cheers and applause]

31:56.966 --> 31:57.848
- thank you. Thank you.

31:57.967 --> 32:03.103
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:03.188 --> 32:07.340
- a writer once said,
"writing is easy.

32:07.443 --> 32:09.509
Just sit at your desk,
open a vein, and bleed."

32:09.612 --> 32:10.944
[audience chuckles]

32:11.030 --> 32:12.679
now, we've all heard
that quote, right?

32:12.781 --> 32:14.448
And it's been attributed
to a lot of people.

32:14.533 --> 32:18.118
But whoever did say it
didn't know the half.

32:18.203 --> 32:19.352
If you want the brass ring,

32:19.455 --> 32:21.955
you better be wearing
brass knuckles.

32:22.041 --> 32:24.691
Greatness comes with a price.

32:24.793 --> 32:26.126
And you just have to
ask yourself,

32:26.211 --> 32:29.463
how much do you want it?

32:29.548 --> 32:30.864
Are you ready to bleed?

32:30.966 --> 32:32.132
<i> [eerie tone]</i>

32:32.217 --> 32:34.868
are you?
All: Yes!

32:34.970 --> 32:38.055
- I'd like all of you to reach
under your seats right now.

32:38.173 --> 32:39.723
Don't be shy.

32:39.842 --> 32:41.642
There's a little something
special under there.

32:41.727 --> 32:43.043
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:43.145 --> 32:45.479
now, it looks like a pill,

32:45.564 --> 32:47.881
but it's not.

32:47.983 --> 32:50.383
It's the key
to condos in malibu,

32:50.486 --> 32:52.218
to dinner meetings
with charlize,

32:52.321 --> 32:54.387
to reservations
at the tower bar.

32:54.490 --> 32:57.157
Tell yourself it's a vitamin.

32:57.242 --> 32:59.826
A sugar pill placebo
packed with satan.

32:59.912 --> 33:01.495
[chuckles]

33:01.580 --> 33:02.996
just don't say no.

33:03.082 --> 33:04.831
- Wait.

33:04.917 --> 33:06.783
I'm sorry,
you didn't tell me about this.

33:06.869 --> 33:09.069
Is this a stimulant?

33:09.171 --> 33:10.070
Because good writers
don't need that.

33:10.172 --> 33:11.905
[scoffs]
I don't need that.

33:12.007 --> 33:13.239
I'm sorry,
we'll take a quick break--

33:13.342 --> 33:15.125
- shut the fuck up,
you hack.

33:15.210 --> 33:17.577
You teach
a screenwriting class.

33:17.680 --> 33:18.244
Have you ever sold
a fucking script?

33:18.347 --> 33:20.747
- Yes.
- One.

33:20.849 --> 33:25.135
A failed orion stallone flick
back in '88?

33:25.220 --> 33:27.087
You know nothing.

33:27.189 --> 33:28.421
I know something.

33:28.524 --> 33:30.807
Would you all rather
listen to me

33:30.893 --> 33:34.427
or this sad,
fraudulent typist?

33:34.530 --> 33:36.096
All: You.

33:36.198 --> 33:38.264
- Everything you've heard
is bullshit.

33:38.367 --> 33:39.933
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:40.035 --> 33:42.652
reality isn't the choice
between the blue pill

33:42.738 --> 33:44.437
and the red pill.

33:44.540 --> 33:45.772
It's the black pill.

33:45.874 --> 33:48.158
This pill.

33:48.243 --> 33:50.994
My special vitamin brain sauce
stimulant

33:51.080 --> 33:53.080
with zero risk
and maximum upside.

33:55.050 --> 33:57.283
I'm gonna tell you a little
something about success

33:57.386 --> 33:59.452
that is the bedrock
of this dirty business

33:59.555 --> 34:01.671
that no one else
wants to admit.

34:01.757 --> 34:04.257
It's just one swallow away.

34:06.895 --> 34:08.812
Spit or swallow--
the choice is yours.

34:15.938 --> 34:20.991
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:24.279 --> 34:25.862
now, as it's going down,

34:25.948 --> 34:27.114
that tingling that you feel?

34:27.199 --> 34:28.865
It's not the pill

34:28.951 --> 34:30.784
and it isn't that food truck
burrito you had for lunch

34:30.869 --> 34:32.035
and it isn't nerves.

34:32.121 --> 34:33.587
It's the future taking hold.

34:36.041 --> 34:37.507
Your future.

34:38.710 --> 34:41.711
- [screaming]

34:41.797 --> 34:44.881
<i> [dramatic eerie music]</i>

34:44.967 --> 34:46.466
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:46.552 --> 34:48.969
- [screams]

34:49.054 --> 34:50.220
<i> - it looks like the streets</i>
<i> are running red</i>

34:50.305 --> 34:52.389
<i> with blood and metaphors.</i>

34:52.474 --> 34:54.141
<i> At least all of those</i>
<i> no-talent monsters</i>

34:54.226 --> 34:56.810
<i> are taking their pain out</i>
<i> in a real way.</i>

34:56.895 --> 35:00.230
<i> Being great is hard.</i>

35:00.315 --> 35:01.565
<i> The rest of us</i>
<i> just don't get it.</i>

35:01.650 --> 35:04.317
<i> We drive ourselves crazy</i>
<i> with envy</i>

35:04.403 --> 35:06.403
<i> longing for just a taste</i>
<i> of the delicious madness</i>

35:06.488 --> 35:08.488
<i> of the creative mind.</i>

35:08.574 --> 35:10.323
<i> But the truth is,</i>

35:10.409 --> 35:12.542
<i> most people aren't willing</i>
<i> to put in the work.</i>

35:12.661 --> 35:15.829
<i> They focus on the success,</i>
<i> the notoriety, the wealth</i>

35:15.914 --> 35:18.331
<i> that their great piece of art</i>
<i> will bring.</i>

35:18.417 --> 35:20.333
<i> But the journey there</i>
<i> is tedious.</i>

35:20.419 --> 35:22.335
<i> And those that achieve</i>
<i> greatness</i>

35:22.421 --> 35:23.837
<i> only do so because</i>
<i> they are fucked up enough</i>

35:23.922 --> 35:25.505
<i> to push through the pain</i>
<i> and failure</i>

35:25.591 --> 35:28.558
<i> it takes to reach</i>
<i> your potential.</i>

35:28.677 --> 35:29.726
<i> At least with these pills</i>
<i> the world can find out</i>

35:29.845 --> 35:31.228
<i> if you're any good.</i>

35:31.346 --> 35:32.896
[baby crying]
- sorry, baby.

35:33.015 --> 35:35.348
Shh, don't cry.

35:35.434 --> 35:37.400
We're gonna move on
to another place,

35:37.519 --> 35:39.402
create another drug--

35:39.521 --> 35:41.238
maybe one that will make
you and I live forever.

35:41.356 --> 35:42.355
<i> [soft music]</i>

35:42.441 --> 35:44.074
mommy's here.

35:44.193 --> 35:46.243
She's on top of it.

35:46.361 --> 35:48.745
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:48.864 --> 35:50.914
<i> - to be told we are talented,</i>

35:51.033 --> 35:52.365
<i> isn't that all we ever want?</i>

35:52.451 --> 35:54.918
[explosion, people scream]

35:55.037 --> 35:57.254
<i> the truth is, history will</i>
<i> only remember a handful of us,</i>

35:57.372 --> 35:59.589
<i> but at least now</i>

35:59.708 --> 36:01.591
<i> we're leveling</i>
<i> the playing field.</i>

36:01.710 --> 36:04.678
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:09.518 --> 36:12.385
<i> [chilling string music]</i>

